data.protoText: Plating 2-5x106 cells in a 60-mm culture dish in 3 ml of medium overnight
Plate cells the night before to give 60-80% confluence at the day of transfection.
Prior to the transfection, change to medium.
Label the small sterile tube and pipet 97μl of serum-free medium and add 3μl of FuGENE 6 directly into the tubes
Add 2µg experimental DNA into the sterile tube
tap the tube or vortex for one second to mix the contents.
Incubate the transfection reagent:DNA complex for minimum of 15 min at room temperature.
add this mixture directly to the cells drop wise through the medium.
Remove growth medium from cultured cells.
Dispense a minimal volume of 1x lysis reagent (RLB; Promega) into each culture vessel
scrape attached cells from the dish
transfer the cells and solution to a micro centrifuge tube.
and transfer the supernatant to a new tube.
Mix 20μl of cell lysate with 100μl of Luciferase Assay Reagent
measure the light produced using LUMAT LB9501 (Berthold, TN).
